setrole
=======

Syntax: setrole <player> <admin|domain|coding|rp>

Sets a wizard's position and synced role tag. The target must be online
and must already be a wizard (position is not "player", "high mortal",
or "ambassador").

  admin   -> arch         [Admin-Wiz]
  domain  -> domain_wiz   [Domain-Wiz]
  coding  -> creator      [Coding-Wiz]
  rp      -> rp_wiz       [RP-Wiz]

Restricted to admin-level wizards. Position and role are saved immediately.

PROMOTING A MORTAL FIRST

If the player is still a mortal, use makewiz before setrole:

  makewiz splynncryth
  setrole splynncryth admin

Or use the Staff of Demotion (type: promote) for a menu-driven approach.

NOTES

  - setrole only works on online players.
  - Use xmote for offline position changes (admin only).
  - All role changes are logged to /log/adm/setrole.

See also: help makewiz, help admin (wizard staff)
